@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    This privacy notice applies to the entirely fictive application known as CaffeineTracker9000, an equally fictive website allegedly operating at a university college called PXL. The supposed goal of CaffeineTracker9000 is to pretend to track caffeine intake among students, staff, night owls, and other legendary beings who survive on coffee during exam periods. No real data is collected, processed, stored, analyzed, enchanted, or teleported elsewhere. Any resemblance to real people, real institutions, real applications, or real consequences is TOTALLY and ABSOLUTELY NOT TRUE.
</p>
<p>
    CaffeineTracker9000 does not collect personal data of any kind. This includes (but is not limited to) names, email addresses, student IDs, IP addresses, preferred coffee strength, number of espressos before debugging works, or how often someone says “this will be my last cup.” There are no cookies, no trackers, no background processes, and certainly no all-seeing eye peering into your mug. Like the One Ring, personal data is far too dangerous to handle — so CaffeineTracker9000 wisely refuses to possess it.
</p>
<p>
    Because no data is collected, no data is shared with anyone. Not with third-party services, not with the university, not with advertisers, and definitely not with dark forces seeking to optimize productivity through caffeine dependency. There are no processors, subprocessors, backups, logs, scrolls, or magical artifacts involved. Even if Saruman himself requested access to the database, he would find nothing but an empty table and a mild sense of disappointment.
</p>
<p>
    As a fictional user of CaffeineTracker9000, you enjoy all possible rights under all applicable and imaginary privacy regulations. These include the right to access your data, correct your data, delete your data, and ceremoniously cast your data into the fires of Mount Doom. Conveniently, since no data exists, all these rights are fulfilled automatically and eternally. If you have any questions about this privacy notice, please remember: the app is not real, the data is not real, and this notice exists purely for educational and humorous purposes. One tracker to rule them all — and in the darkness store absolutely nothing.
</p>
